-- Brazil’s Globo Hires Banks to Arrange Bond Investor Meetings
-- B y   V e r o n i c a   N a v a r r o   E s p i n o s a
-- 2012-03-29T12:23:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-29/brazil-s-globo-hires-banks-to-arrange-bond-investor-meetings.html
Globo Comunicacoes e Participacoes
SA,  Brazil ’s biggest television network, hired HSBC Holdings Plc
and Itau Unibanco Holding SA to arrange meetings with bond
investors, according to a person familiar with the discussions.  Globo plans to meet investors in London, New York and
Boston next week, said the person, who asked not to be
identified because the discussions are private.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Veronica Navarro Espinosa in New York at 
 vespinosa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
